  "overview": {
    "summary": "Peggle Krastov is a Goliath, Bear Totem Barbarian from the North Bjornguard. In search of inheritance from his noble family, and for the sake of his niece, he consulted the best anger management in Solstitheo, inside the Immortal City of Edelith. he is a man guided by a strong moral compass, and to find a way to suppress his anger. After finding out Vaskel Krastov from the Iron Fang Sect is in Edelith, he left the main party to reassess his priorities and to grow stronger in fear his plans are to kill him, or harm his family as his ultimate goal.",
     "personality": "Peggle is a kind, but hardy soul that refuses to yield and bow to anyone aside from family. The only thing stopping him is his own anger and temperment and now seeks a therapist who can help him control his anger, so he may be the best Uncle to his neice.",
    "likes":    ["Tea", "Broomhilda's Cookies", "Gambling", "Dominant Women"],
    "dislikes": ["Absolutes", "Playing with lives", "Carriage Kin", "Vaskel Krastov"],
    "trivia": [
      { "text": "In Bjornguard culture, the rite to adulthood is to go on your first solo hunt, and wearing the pelt of your first kill into adulthoold, hence the bear.", "redacted": false },
      { "text": "It's been revealed by Pazenless in Gratehaven, that the Guns are of divine origin rather than the preassumed infernal.", "redacted": true },
      { "text": "Blaze has markings on his back which are usually invisible to the naked eye.", "redacted": true },
      { "text": "Earned the name Blaze during his years on the farm when he tried to use his burgeoning hellfire to instantly brand a rowdy bull; he missed, torched the barn's winter hay supply, and spent the next three days sweeping ash out of his father's boots.", "redacted": true }
    ],
    "sideQuote": "If your plan is to use people, i will kill you."
  },

